   {
      "body" : "After discussion on IRC:\r\n```\r\n20:39:31 < sipa> sdaftuar: in general, peers should not send getblocktxn for anything near the tip\r\n20:39:40 < sipa> *anything not near the tip\r\n20:39:51 < sdaftuar> right, agreed\r\n20:40:00 < sdaftuar> are you suggesting that we disconnect for old blocks as wel?\r\n20:40:09 < sdaftuar> rather than not disconnect for unknown blocks?\r\n20:40:37 < sipa> if they do, they're either confused (and they're better off with us disconnecting them, or they'll wait long before timing out) or trying to do something nasty (in which case we're better off disconnecting them)\r\n20:40:58 < sipa> the question is whether there are no cases under which this can happen accidentally\r\n20:41:11 < sdaftuar> i assumed naively that this could happen on testnet\r\n20:41:32 < sdaftuar> ie without much rigorous thought\r\n20:41:54 < sdaftuar> mostly i guess i was comparing the handling of getblocktxn to how we handle getdata requests\r\n20:42:33 < sdaftuar> where we silently ignore unknown, and non-main-chain old blocks\r\n20:43:03 < sipa> ok, in that case let's follow the same approach\r\n```\r\n",
